claim.claim-text:
35. A method of bonding multiple layers, the method comprising the steps of: 
depositing each of the multiple layers in a NaOH:H2O2:H2O (5:1:1) solution at 80° Celsius; 
depositing each of the multiple layers in a H2SO4:H2O (5:1) solution at 80° Celsius; 
pressing the multiple layers together to form a stack; and 
volumetrically heating the stack to a predetermined temperature.
